{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"e3yh106bjbj4yim4rsaulv6","title":"Collections Class","desc":"","updated":1713633743321,"created":1713627118031,"custom":{},"fname":"lang.java.lib.collection.s","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"cs"},"contentHash":"43538fc6378725efacdbb31fd02029cd","links":[{"from":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.collection.cheatsheet","id":"fi3xznhjsf8ezkolih7torp","vaultName":"cs"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":45,"column":5,"offset":2172},"end":{"line":45,"column":35,"offset":2202},"indent":[]},"value":"lang.java.lib.collection.s"}],"anchors":{"size-of-collection-objects":{"type":"header","text":"Size of Collection Objects","value":"size-of-collection-objects","line":10,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"dkdtvct3q6f8lggmoqrqf43","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"collections-class\">Collections Class<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#collections-class\"></a></h1>\n<p>Utility class (<code>java.util.package</code>) which defines several methods for collection objects.</p>\n<h2 id=\"size-of-collection-objects\">Size of Collection Objects<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#size-of-collection-objects\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Default Initial Capacity</strong></p>\n<p>  The initial capacity assigned to a Collection class object by default, if not specified while initializing the object.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Fill Ratio/Load Factor</strong></p>\n<p>  The percentage or ratio of capacity which when reached will result in increasing of the capacity.</p>\n<p>  For example, if the initial default capacity is 10 and fill ratio is 0.7 - the capacity will increase once 7 places are filled.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Reaches Max Cap → New AL object created with new capacity → all objects copied</p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/cs/notes/fi3xznhjsf8ezkolih7torp\">Collection Frameworks Cheatsheet (cs)</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex